lapsed_t1_262a" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_262a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 June 2010 10:51:25AM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_262a'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_262a')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_262a" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_262a" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Morendil/">Morendil</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 June 2010 10:51:25AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_262a'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_262a'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_262a')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_262a" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>Everyone who takes basic statistics has it drilled into them that "correlation is not causation." (When I took psych. 1, the professor said he hoped that, if he were to come to us on our death-beds and prompt us with "Correlation is," we would <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/k5/cached_thoughts/">all respond</a> "not causation.") This is a problem, because one can infer correlation from data, and would like to be able to make inferences about causation. There are typically two ways out of this. One is to perform an experiment, preferably a randomized double-blind experiment, to eliminate accidental sources of correlation, common causes, etc. That's nice when you can do it, but impossible with supernovae, and not even easy with people. The other out is to look for correlations, say that of course they don't equal causations, and then act as if they did anyway.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Cosma Shalizi on <a href="http://cscs.umich.edu/~crshalizi/notebooks/graphical-models.html" rel="nofollow">Graphical Models</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_262a"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_262a" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_262a')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_262a" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_262a')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_262a" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/262a?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_262a" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_262a')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_262a class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_262a" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_262a" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_262a" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_262d" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_262d" class="parent"><a name="262d" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_262d" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_262d" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_262d" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 June 2010 11:12:01AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_262d'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_262d')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_262d" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_262d" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">19 June 2010 11:12:01AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_262d'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_262d'] = ['-1 points', 