<p>Succinctly stated. I love it.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2632"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2632" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2632')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2632" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2632')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2632" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/2632?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2632" href="#2625" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2632" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2632')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2632 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2632" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_24f3" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_24f3" class="parent"><a name="24f3" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_24f3" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_24f3" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_24f3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jack/">Jack</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 05:56:42AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24f3'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_24f3')">[+] (4 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_24f3" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_24f3" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Jack/">Jack</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 05:56:42AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_24f3'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24f3'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_24f3')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_24f3" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>This seems... confused. The is-ought distinction is the distinction between preference and fact.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_24f3"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_24f3" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24f3')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_24f3" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24f3')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_24f3" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/24f3?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_24f3" href="#24f2" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_24f3" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_24f3')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_24f3 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_24f3" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_24f3" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_24f3" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_24gn" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_24gn" class="parent"><a name="24gn" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_24gn" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_24gn" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_24gn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 03:30:43PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24gn'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_24gn')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_24gn" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_24gn" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/CronoDAS/">CronoDAS</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 03:30:43PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_24gn'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24gn'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_24gn')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_24gn" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>"Preferences" are also facts about minds.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_24gn"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_24gn" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24gn')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_24gn" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24gn')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_24gn" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/24gn?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_24gn" href="#24f3" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_24gn" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_24gn')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_24gn class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_24gn" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_24gn" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_24gn" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_24gs" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_24gs" class="parent"><a name="24gs" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_24gs" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_24gs" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_24gs" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 03:36:48PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24gs'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_24gs')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_24gs" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_24gs" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Vladimir_Nesov/">Vladimir_Nesov</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 03:36:48PM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_24gs'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24gs'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_24gs')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_24gs" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>"Preferences" are also facts about minds.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Not directly, there is no fixed "preference mapping" from minds to preferences that works in general. We can only hope for one that works for humans, constructed for searching preference of humans, because it won't need to work for any almost-humans or not-humans-at-all. I look at a mind and see that its preference is X, you look at the same mind and say it's Y. There is no factual disagreement, the sense of "preference" was different; and if it was the same, the purpose was lost.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_24gs"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_24gs" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24gs')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_24gs" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24gs')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_24gs" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/24gs?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_24gs" href="#24gn" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_24gs" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_24gs')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_24gs class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_24gs" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_24gs" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_24gs" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_252w" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_252w" class="parent"><a name="252w" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_252w" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_252w" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_252w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Simulation_Brain/">Simulation_Brain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 June 2010 06:37:25AM</span><span class="votes " >0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_252w'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_252w')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_252w" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_252w" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Simulation_Brain/">Simulation_Brain</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">12 June 2010 06:37:25AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_252w'>0 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_252w'] = ['-1 points', '0 points', '1 point' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_252w')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_252w" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Well, yes; it's not straightforward to go from brains to preferences.  But for any particular definition of preference, a given brain's "preference" is just a fact about that brain.  If this is true, it's important to understanding morality/ethics/volition.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_252w"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_252w" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_252w')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_252w" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_252w')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_252w" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/252w?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_252w" href="#24gs" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_252w" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_252w')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_252w class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_252w" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_252w" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_252w" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_26jj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_26jj" class="parent"><a name="26jj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_26jj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_26jj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comme