iv id="entry_t1_248m" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_248m" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_248m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 June 2010 05:43:12AM</span><span class="votes " >3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_248m'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_248m')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_248m" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_248m" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">07 June 2010 05:43:12AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_248m'>3 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_248m'] = ['2 points', '3 points', '4 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_248m')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_248m" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Whoever it was, it was clearly someone who has never proved a theorem.</p>

<p>Ok, in <a href="http://www.believermag.com/issues/200508/?read=interview_haidt" rel="nofollow">context</a> he's talking about moral beliefs, but still.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_248m"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_248m" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_248m')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_248m" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_248m')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_248m" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/248m?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_248m" href="#248l" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_248m" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_248m')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_248m class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_248m" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_248m" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_248m" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_25wj" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_25wj" class="parent"><a name="25wj" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_25wj" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_25wj" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_25wj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 June 2010 12:57:20PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_25wj'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_25wj')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_25wj" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_25wj" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/wedrifid/">wedrifid</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">18 June 2010 12:57:20PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_25wj'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_25wj'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_25wj')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_25wj" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>We could say (with some degree of insight) that proving a theorem is something that the "press secretary" sometimes does as a hobby in its off hours.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_25wj"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_25wj" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_25wj')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_25wj" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_25wj')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_25wj" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/25wj?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_25wj" href="#248m" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_25wj" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_25wj')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_25wj class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_25wj" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_23mh" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_23mh" class="parent"><a name="23mh" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_23mh" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_23mh" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_23mh" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Seth_Goldin/">Seth_Goldin</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 June 2010 03:40:44AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >14 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23mh'] = ['13 points', '14 points', '15 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_23mh')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_23mh" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_23mh" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Seth_Goldin/">Seth_Goldin</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 June 2010 03:40:44AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_23mh'>14 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23mh'] = ['13 points', '14 points', '15 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_23mh')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_23mh" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>There is no such thing as absolute certainty, but there is assurance sufficient for the purposes of human life.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>John Stuart Mill, <em>On Liberty</em></p>

<p>He seems to have understood that <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/mp/0_and_1_are_not_probabilities/">0 and 1 are not probabilities</a>.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_23mh"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_23mh" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23mh')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_23mh" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23mh')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_23mh" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/23mh?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_23mh" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_23mh')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_23mh class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_23mh" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_23mh" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_23mh" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_243y" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_243y" class="parent"><a name="243y" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_243y" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_243y" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_243y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Warrigal/">Warrigal</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 June 2010 08:43:49PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_243y'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_243y')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_243y" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_243y" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Warrigal/">Warrigal</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">05 June 2010 08:43:49PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_243y'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_243y'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_243y')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_243y" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>You know, that post is somewhat annoyingly titled. 0 and 1 are probabilities by the common definition of "probability", but defining "probability" such that 0 and 1 are not probabilities results in a system which is also consistent and useful.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_243y"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_243y" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_243y')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_243y" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_243y')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_243y" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/243y?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_243y" href="#23mh" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_243y" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_243y')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_243y class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_243y" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_23nm" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_23nm" class="parent"><a name="23nm" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_23nm" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_23nm" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_23nm" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/toto/">toto</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">03 June 2010 09:29:12AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23nm'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class=