iv id="body_t1_24gr" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I would prefer to say that conforming your thoughts to reality is science, and conforming reality to your thoughts is engineering...</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_24gr"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_24gr" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24gr')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_24gr" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_24gr')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_24gr" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/24gr?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_24gr" href="#23bp" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_24gr" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_24gr')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_24gr class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_24gr" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_24gr" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_24gr" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_24gv" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_24gv" class="parent"><a name="24gv" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_24gv" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_24gv" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_24gv" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 04:46:39PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24gv'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_24gv')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_24gv" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_24gv" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/RichardKennaway/">RichardKennaway</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">08 June 2010 04:46:39PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_24gv'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_24gv'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_24gv')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_24gv" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Putting those together, science is sanity and engineering is creativity. Or to merge this with an aphorism of George Bernard Shaw, science sees things and asks "why?", and engineering dreams things that never were and asks "why not!"</p>

