  <p>Using language that is appropriate in one linguistic framework in a different linguistic framework is what causes philosophical confusion and pseudo puzzles, also known as the history of philosophy.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>-- Thomas Cathcart &amp; Daniel Klein, <em>Plato and a Platypus Walk into a Bar... : Understanding Philosophy Through Jokes</em></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_23b8"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_23b8" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23b8')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_23b8" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23b8')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_23b8" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/23b8?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_23b8" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_23b8')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_23b8 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_23b8" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_23b8" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_23b8" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_23c1" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_23c1" class="parent"><a name="23c1" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_23c1" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_23c1" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_23c1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nic_Smith/">Nic_Smith</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 June 2010 05:14:01AM</span><span class="votes " >6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23c1'] = ['5 points', '6 points', '7 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_23c1')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_23c1" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_23c1" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Nic_Smith/">Nic_Smith</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 June 2010 05:14:01AM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_23c1'>6 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23c1'] = ['5 points', '6