ass="author"><a id="author_t1_23aa" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/orangecat/">orangecat</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">02 June 2010 12:29:45AM<em>*</em>&nbsp;</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_23aa'>9 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23aa'] = ['8 points', '9 points', '10 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_23aa')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_23aa" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>I reject that entirely," said Dirk, sharply. "The impossible often has a kind of integrity to it which the merely improbable lacks. How often have you been presented with an apparently rational explanation of something which works in all respects other than one, which is just that it is hopelessly improbable? Your instinct is to say, `Yes, but he or she simply wouldn't do that.'"</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Douglas Adams</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_23aa"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_23aa" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23aa')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_23aa" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23aa')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_23aa" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/23aa?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_23aa" href="#236n" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_23aa" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_23aa')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_23aa class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_23aa" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_237u" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_237u" class="parent"><a name="237u" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_237u" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_237u" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_237u" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Oscar_Cunningham/">Oscar_Cunningham</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 08:16:43PM</span><span class="votes " >14 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_237u'] = ['13 points', '14 points', '15 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_237u')">[+] (3 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_237u" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_237u" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/Oscar_Cunningham/">Oscar_Cunningham</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 08:16:43PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_237u'>14 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_237u'] = ['13 points', '14 points', '15 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_237u')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_237u" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>...Or you've just missed something. If all you're left with is improbable <a href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/if/your_strength_as_a_rationalist/">you <em>notice that you are confused</em></a>. I've always thought that quote was off.</p>

