ective.</a></p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_2391"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_2391" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2391')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_2391" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_2391')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_2391" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/2391?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_2391" href="#237r" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_2391" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_2391')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_2391 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_2391" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_236h" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_236h" class="parent"><a name="236h" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_236h" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_236h" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_236h" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 06:31:48PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_236h'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_236h')">[+] (2 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_236h" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_236h" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 06:31:48PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_236h'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_236h'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_236h')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_236h" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
  <p>The unconscious naturally weights the relative importance of various attributes. Conscious 
  thought often leads to suboptimal weighting because it disturbs this natural process. --Ap Dijksterhuis</p>
</blockquote></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_236h"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_236h" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_236h')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_236h" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_236h')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_236h" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/236h?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_236h" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_236h')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_236h class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_236h" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_236h" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_236h" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_23a0" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_23a0" class="parent"><a name="23a0" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_23a0" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_23a0" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_23a0" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 11:35:55PM</span><span class="votes " >2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23a0'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_23a0')">[+] (1 child)</a></div><div id="display_t1_23a0" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_23a0" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/JoshuaZ/">JoshuaZ</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 11:35:55PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_23a0'>2 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23a0'] = ['1 point', '2 points', '3 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_23a0')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_23a0" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>I'm not sure this is a very rationalist quote. In particular, many judgments people make and many biases come into play at a non-conscious level. We generally need to make a conscious effort to correct for those biases.</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_23a0"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_23a0" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23a0')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_23a0" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23a0')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_23a0" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/23a0?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_23a0" href="#236h" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_23a0" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_23a0')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_23a0 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_23a0" class="child" ><div id="siteTable_t1_23a0" class="sitetable"><div id="ajaxHook_t1_23a0" class="ajaxhook"></div><div id="thingrow_t1_23a5" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_23a5" class="parent"><a name="23a5" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_23a5" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_23a5" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_23a5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 11:45:11PM</span><span class="votes " >4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23a5'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_23a5')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_23a5" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_23a5" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 11:45:11PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_23a5'>4 points</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_23a5'] = ['3 points', '4 points', '5 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_23a5')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_23a5" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><p>Yes and no. You are right about a lot of  biases originating from the unconscious. But the other way is also possible, the smart human who does something stupid because he has a good theory of how it should be done. Or choosing a picture because of some salient verbalizable reason instead of just taking the one you like the most without necessarily being able to explain why, etc...</p>

<p>There is more on this topic in "The rational unconscious: Conscious versus unconscious thought in complex 
consumer choice" by Ap Dijksterhuis and in Jonah Lehrer "How we decide".</p></div></div><div style="display: none;" id="edit_body_t1_23a5"></div><div class="comment-links"><ul class="clear"><li class="first"><a id="up_t1_23a5" class="up" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23a5')" >Vote up</a></li><li><a id="down_t1_23a5" class="down" onclick="showcover(true, 'vote_t1_23a5')" >Vote down</a></li><li><a id="permalink_t1_23a5" href="http://lesswrong.com/lw/2ay/rationality_quotes_june_2010/23a5?c=1" class=" " target="_parent" >Permalink</a></li><li><a id="parent_t1_23a5" href="#23a0" class="bylink">Parent</a></li><li><a id="reply_a_t1_23a5" class="" href="javascript:reply('t1_23a5')">Reply</a></li></ul><span id=status_t1_23a5 class="error" style="display: none;"></span></div></div></div><div id="child_t1_23a5" class="child" ></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div></div><div class="clearleft"><!--IE6sux--></div><div id="thingrow_t1_236g" class="comment" ><div id="pre_t1_236g" class="parent"><a name="236g" ></a></div><div id="entry_t1_236g" class="entry"><div id="collapsed_t1_236g" class="comment-meta collapsed clear " style='display:none'><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author gray"><a id="author_t1_236g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 06:31:12PM</span><span class="votes " >1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_236g'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return showcomment('t1_236g')">[+] (0 children)</a></div><div id="display_t1_236g" class="" ><div class="comment-meta clear"><span class="comment-author"><strong><span class="author"><a id="author_t1_236g" href="http://lesswrong.com/user/roland/">roland</a></span></strong></span><span class="comment-date">01 June 2010 06:31:12PM</span><span class="votes " id='score_t1_236g'>1 point</span><script type="text/javascript">vl['t1_236g'] = ['0 points', '1 point', '2 points' ];</script>&#32;<a href="#" class="expand" onclick="return hidecomment('t1_236g')">[-]</a></div><div id="body_t1_236g" class="comment-content"><div class="md"><blockquote>
